begin_memory_text: We talked about where we were chatting from but because we had a common love of teaching and the craziness that COVID 19 is causing, we had so much to talk about.  We stay on the same subject.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation, she was explaining her schedule and the frustrations that as a teacher in New York City, how to juggle all the things being thrown her way.  I was asking if a parent or PTAcould support teachers by maybe reviewing technology for her.
end_memory_text: Towards the end of the conversation we were still talking about education but now wondering if this group of people in the world, will it show up on jobs and life and abilities or will if not really matter that they aren't getting the "education" being in school.
rest_of_day_open: The rest of the week I see myself completing at least 2 more house projects that I delved into when the pandemic started.  I also see me putting in orders for supplies thinking that numbers are going up and we want to make sure that we do not have to go out and pick up even essentials.  I also see myself doing more surveys.
critical_positive: The fact that we were both teachers at some point in our lives, we had similar opinions about what is important in education.  I also could soooo relate to what she must be going through as a teacher during a pandemic so she was freely able to talk about her frustrations.  I hope I added and made her think about some of the things that might help her as she continues this year as a teacher.  I really liked talking to her.
critical_negative: The only thing I can think of was that the reverb of me speaking from her computer was annoying.  Mine probably did the same thing since we did not have earbuds or microphones at our disposal.  I felt we interacted very smoothly and friendly because the topic was both something we had done in our lives.  I would have liked to find out about her travels but we never got to that.

begin_memory_text: At the very beginning it was a little awkward because we were talking over each other and I wasn't sure if we should say our names or introduce ourselves, but we quickly latched on to both our connections to teaching/education and it was easy to go from there.
middle_memory_text: We had a lot to say about the state of education today when it comes to remote learning and how the pandemic is affecting students, especially student equity.
end_memory_text: We talked about the future of education and how teachers have been doing so much to adapt to the situation. We talked about the hope that maybe standardized testing will give way to a more robust project-based holistic grading system.
rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of the week will provide a much needed respite from the craziness and stress of the previous week. Work has been extremely overwhelming but I think I will be able to find peace and solace in the weekend, spending time with my husband, and following through on some plans I have to go to a museum.
critical_positive: What worked well was that we had a lot in common because we both had a lot of interest in education. I'm a teacher and she used to be a teacher, and is now very active in her son's education. We have a lot of the same opinions about the state of education right now and feel the same about how to manage the pandemic when it comes to learning.
critical_negative: I didn't really learn anything about her other than how she feels about education. At times it occurred to me that I have no idea about her politics, her marital status, or anything like that. Even though we agreed with each other a lot one point I wondered if maybe we had the complete opposite opinion about politics and how I still don't really know her as a whole person.
